author: @itsme133
text:
For new fans: 
(in age order)


Scoups(Seungcheol): All white outfit, white buckethat with black writing on it
Jeonghan: grey-greenish pants, white shirt under black and white jacket, maroon hair
Joshua: Blue jans, grey/red/black balenciaga jakcet
Jun(Junhui): Blue cargo pants, white musle shirt, redish hair
Hoshi(Soonyoung): Complete tye-dye outfit, red cap
Wonwoo: White sweatpants, teal shirt, black cap and black mask on chin
Woozi(Jihoon): Black shorts with white design, white shirt with white with black stiped jacket on top, black cap
DK(Dokyeom/Seokmin): Grey jeans, white shirt under grey jean jacket, grey bucket hat
Mingyu: Beieg pants white muscle shirt with '2020' in red on front, black bucket hat
The8(Minghao): Entire camo outfit, black cap
Seungkwan: Blue sweatpants, white tshirt, teal cap
Vernon(Hansol): Entire black outfit, black beanie
Dino(Chan): Black pants, white/yellow/black jacket

Scoups is the leader
Units are: 
Hiphop unit: Scoups, Wonwoo, Mingyu, Vernon
Performnce Unit: Hoshi,Jun, The8, Dino
Vocal Unit: Joshua, Jeonghan, Woozi, Dokyeom, Seungkwan

Enjoy!

author: @pdfafileforstorage2
text:
This choreography just barely beat out HIT for favourite Seventeen choreography.

Reasons
*1.* Obviously, the synchronization. I mean, it's Seventeen. What do you expect?? LOL
*2.* Some parts of the choreography are just absolutely creative. A relay race during Vernon's part, Wonwoo (athlete) high-fiving some of the members in line (the audience) during his second verse, Woozi running off track but DK pushes him back at the bridge of the song. All of these add to the theme behind Left & Right.
*3.* A lot of the choreography is just having fun like during Vernon's verse and Joshua's part in the final chorus. Their screams and shouts really help with that.

author: @hio7816
text:
If someone will ask "why this is qualified for the dance performance award when it is very easy to dance?" , answer this:

1.) The only easy part is the first part of the chorus. The second part is hard (especially in a close formation).
2. The second part is hard but the verses are harder.
3. The making of the formations while doing those wide movements are the hardest because the movements are really wide, the formations are pretty close, and the formations changes all the time.
4. This is a very creative dance routine, the formations are on point, it really complements to the sound and lyrics of the song, and it also relay the message of the song.
5. It's easy to dance but hard to perfect (the vibe, joy, the members movements, and the whole thing.)
6. It is catchy and very difficult to pull off at the same time.
8. While the other members are not on the focus, they still have choreography to do, which is really nice. 
9. They really deserve the award.

author: @ratdeul323
text:
Even tho this choreo doesn't require that much strength, but still they did a lot of unique things with formations like in the beginning they make a line, square and a circle. Also they added the concept of race pretty effectively like the 01:21 relay race, wonwoo doing the countdown, 02:35 when woozi gets off track but is pushed back to the lane meaning that you could screw up sometime, just get back to the right path, 00:53 seungkwan drinking probably a sports drink or booster whatever you call it, 01:43 wonu touching the hands in line could be a reference when athletes win they touch the hands of audience or other players in the line.
Basically if you see, how fun and creative this choreo is not just moves thrown together.
02:16 my personal fav step, how in smoothly they just come into that formation, wow that transition. I also love how they use levels to captivate your attention to the member they want, and the most lovely thing about this choreo is SMILEY SEVENTEEN.

author: @Haley-td8ui
text:
this has got to be my favorite comeback since Thanks! of course i still love all of their previous comebacks but there's just something about Left & Right that brings out the best in SEVENTEEN. this choreography video really shows how much fun they're having with this comeback. the little shouts and 'ayy's that they do throughout the entire thing, along with the smiles that never leave their faces, really make me so happy because it shows that you don't always need difficult choreographies to stand out amongst a million other groups. SEVENTEEN earned a lot more fans during this comeback because of the vibe they give off and it showed the newcomers their personalities and that they truly love doing what they're doing. so yeah, this is 100% my favorite comeback yet. 

stan seventeen if you haven't already :)

text:
*For new carats!* 💎

Woozi - black shorts/white jacket, vocal team leader, producer
Vernon - all black with beanie, 1/2 of the American line, hip-hop (rap) team
The8 - matching patterned hoodie/ shorts & black hat, 1/2 of the Chinese line, performance team

Joshua - gray/black jacket & jeans, 1/2 of the American line, vocal team
Jeonghan - black/white jacket & gray pants, vocal team
Hoshi - pastel outfit, performance team leader, keeps everyone synchronized
S.coups - all white & bucket hat, hip-hop (rap) team leader + main leader
Mingyu - 2020 tank, hip-hop (rap) team
Jun - blue pants & white tank, 1/2 of the Chinese line, performance team
Wonwoo - light blue shirt & white pants, hip-hop (rap) team
DK - gray jacket/pants & bucket hat, vocal team
Seungkwan - white shirt & light blue hat, vocal team

Hope this can help someone! If it did, welcome to the family! 💖

text:
i saw this on twitter but it doesn't have that many rt so i'm telling yall here

during vernon's rap verse, he passed the baton to minghao by highfiving him. the last runner of the relay was joshua and woozi was the hurdle. at the same time, thoe other boys can be seen supporting the runner. you could tell the team won the race when vernon raised joshua's arm.

this information was not important to me but i think this story adds depth to the whole choreography and it's so beautiful. in conclusion, seventeen best artists. seventeen world domination.

thanks for coming to my TED talk. stan seventeen.

author: @wafiqilman5182
text:
SEVENTEEN berhasil memecahkan rekor mereka sendiri dengan penjualan album barunya.

Hanya dalam waktu 4 hari sejak dirilis pada 22 Juni 2020 lalu, mini album ‘Heng:garæ’ sudah berhasil memecahkan rekor penjualan album SEVENTEEN dalam seminggu.

 

Menurut data dari Hanteo Chart, mini album ‘Heng:garæ’ berhasil terjual sebanyak 895.230 keping pada 25 Juni 2020 atau empat hari setelah dirilis.

Angka tersebut berhasil melampaui rekor penjualan album ‘An Ode’ yang pada tahun 2019 lalu berhasil terjual sebanyak 700.863 keping dalam waktu seminggu.

Karena baru empat hari sejak dirilis, maka kemungkinan besar mini album ‘Heng:garæ’ akan mendapatkan angka penjualan yang lebih tinggi di minggu pertama rilis.

‘Heng:garæ’ juga menjadi album kedua yang mendapatkan penjualan tertinggi pada minggu pertama di tahun 2020, tepat di bawah album ‘Map of the Soul: 7’ milik BTS.

Selamat kepada SEVENTEEN!
